2019-03-26

	* po2bats 0.1.1: Revision: 0.1.3: Update project.  by kim  <kimkim19642004@yahoo.co.jp>
		Reason for Update:
			- Fixed minor description errors.

		Tested platforms:
			Fedora 29:
				(Step 1) Installing and updating basic software
					sudo dnf install dnf-plugins-extras-tracer
					sudo dnf upgrade
					(If necessary, reboot your system or login again.)
					
					sudo dnf install bats moreutils kcov shellcheck
				(Step 2) Localization (Example: Japanese)
					sudo dnf install man-pages-ja
				(Step 3) Download this software
					cd $HOME
					git clone https://github.com/kimkim19642004/po2bats-autotools.git
				(Step 4) Normal installation procedure for this software
					cd $HOME/po2bats-autotools

					(The following is required only after the initial 'git clone'.)
					(Match the timestamps of the following files with the rules described in 'Makefile'.)
					touch aclocal.m4 Makefile.in

					./configure && make
					sudo make install
				(Step 5) Full installation procedure for this software (If you need to rebuild this software)
					sudo dnf install autoconf-archive
					cd $HOME/po2bats-autotools
					gettextize -f
					autoreconf -f -i
					./configure && make
					make check
					make distcheck
					sudo make install
					make installcheck

			openSUSE Tumbleweed:
				(Step 1) Installing and updating basic software
					sudo zypper dup
					sudo zypper inr
					sudo zypper refresh
					sudo zypper update
					sudo zypper install --type pattern devel_basis
					sudo zypper install expect
					sudo zypper install autoconf-archive bats moreutils ShellCheck
					cd $HOME
					git clone https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov.git
					sudo zypper install cmake libcurl-devel libelf-devel libdw-devel
					cd kcov
					mkdir build
				cd build
				cmake ..
				make
				sudo make install

			[GhostBSD 18.12](https://ghostbsd.org/):
				(Step 1) Specify 'bash' as MATE terminal when installing this distoribution.
				(Step 2) Installing and updating basic software
					sudo trueos-update check
					sudo trueos-update upgrade
					sudo pkg update
					sudo pkg upgrade
					sudo pkg install autotools expect
					sudo pkg install coreutils autoconf-archive bats-core moreutils hs-ShellCheck
					git clone https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov.git
					sudo pkg install binutils cmake elfutils python
					cd kcov
					mkdir build
					cd build
					cmake ..
					make
					sudo make install
				(Step 3) Create symbolic links to GNU commands with 'g' prefix as follows:
					sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/gmktemp /usr/local/bin/mktemp
					sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/grealpath /usr/local/bin/realpath
					sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/gsha256sum /usr/local/bin/sha256sum
					sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/gchmod /usr/local/bin/chmod
					sudo ln -s /usr/local/bin/gmv /usr/local/bin/mv
				(Step 4) In the file "$HOME/.bashrc", change the PATH environment variable as follows:
					BATS_ROOT="/usr/local"
					PATH="/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/games:/usr/bin:/usr/sbin:/bin:/sbin"
					PATH="$BATS_ROOT/libexec/bats-core:$PATH"
					export BATS_ROOT
					export PATH

			[Windows Subsystem for Linux] (base on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS) on Windows 10:
				(Step 1) Installing and updating basic software
					cd $HOME
					sudo apt update
					sudo apt upgrade
					sudo apt install build-essential cmake python gettext
					sudo apt install binutils-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev zlib1g-dev libdw-dev libiberty-dev
					sudo apt install autoconf-archive bats moreutils shellcheck
					git clone https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov/
					cd kcov
					mkdir build
					cd build
					cmake ..
					make
					sudo make install
				(Step 2) Localization (Example: Japanese)
					sudo apt install language-pack-ja
					sudo update-locale LANG=ja_JP.UTF8
					(Please restart Ubuntu here...)
					sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
					sudo apt install manpages-ja manpages-ja-dev
				(Step 3) Full installation
					cd $HOME
					git clone https://github.com/kimkim19642004/po2bats-autotools.git
					cd po2bats-autotools
					sudo dnf install autopoint expect
					./gettextize.exp
					autoreconf -f -i
					./configure && make
					make check
					make distcheck
					sudo make install
					make installcheck
				(Step 4) Display coverage measurement result
					The easiest way:
						1. cp -r coverage /mnt/c/Users/<username>/<dir>
						2. Open file '/mnt/c/Users/<username>/<dir>/coverage/index.html' by 'Microsoft Edge'.
					How to check the coverage result on the Ubuntu desktop:
						1. Install and launch [VcXsrv Windows X Server](https://sourceforge.net/projects/vcxsrv/).
						2. Add 'export DISPLAY=:0.0' to '.bashrc'.
						3. Restart 'Ubuntu'.
						3. sudo apt install lxde (You will have to wait an hour or so...)
						4. Open 'coverage/index.html' with 'Firefox'.

			[Basix 4.0](http://simosnet.com/livecdroom/) (base on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS):
				(Step 1) Installing and updating basic software
					sudo apt update
					sudo apt upgrade
				(Step 2) Normal installation procedure for this software
					cd $HOME
					git clone https://github.com/kimkim19642004/po2bats-autotools.git
				sudo apt install autoconf-archive bats moreutils kcov shellcheck
				(Note 1)
					If there is any problem with the package installed by the command 'sudo apt install kcov',
					try installing 'kcov' from https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov/.
					In that case also run the following command: sudo apt install build-essential cmake
				(Note 2)
					Since the versions of 'automake' is old,
					reconfigure this build system before execute the command './ configure && make'.
					Execute as follows:
						sudo apt install autopoint expect
						./gettextize.exp
						autoreconf -f -i
						./ configure && make
				(URL)
					http://simosnet.com/livecdroom/Ubuntu 18.04 LTS)

			Ubuntu 16.04 LTS (on Travis CI):
				sudo apt update
				sudo apt upgrade (This process is time consuming and is not recommended on Travis CI.)
				sudo apt install autoconf-archive bats moreutils kcov shellcheck
				(Note 1)
					If there is any problem with the package installed by the command 'sudo apt install kcov',
					try installing 'kcov' from https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov/.
				(Note 2)
					Since the versions of 'automake' and 'gettext' are old,
					reconfigure this build system before execute the command './ configure && make'.
					Execute as follows:
						sudo apt install autopoint expect
						./gettextize.exp
						autoreconf -f -i
						./ configure && make
				(URL)
					https://travis-ci.com/kimkim19642004/po2bats-autotools

			Mac OS X 10.13, Xcode 9.4.1 (on Travis CI):
				brew upgrade (This process is time consuming and is not recommended on Travis CI.)
				brew install autoconf-archive bats-core moreutils kcov shellcheck gnu-getopt
				brew link --force gettext
				export PATH=$(brew --prefix coreutils)/libexec/gnubin:$PATH
				export MANPATH=$(brew --prefix coreutils)/libexec/gnubin:$MANPATH
				export PATH="/usr/local/opt/gnu-getopt/bin:$PATH"
				(Note 1)
					If there is any problem with the package installed by the command 'brew install kcov',
					try installing 'kcov' from https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov/.
				(Note 2)
					 Refused command (Old command): brew link --force gnu-getopt
					 Alternate command: export PATH="/usr/local/opt/gnu-getopt/bin:$PATH"
				(URL)
					https://travis-ci.com/kimkim19642004/po2bats-autotools
